{"id": "duc04-testb-26:6#19", "contents": "The conference, organized by the Medical Research Council, brought together local and international experts to discuss mental health issues related to the Truth Commission's work. Villa-Vicencio stressed the need for tolerance in dealing with those who committed crimes, acknowledging that the potential for wrongdoing exists in everyone. He stated that the entire human race carries the capacity for evil, highlighting the importance of understanding and addressing the root causes of such actions. The conference also touched on the case of Eugene de Kock, a police death squad leader who has applied for amnesty for his crimes."}
